{
  "texts": [
    "Each of them corresponds to a path on the Stokes diagram of Θ.",
    "Via the Legendre transform, this path can be transported to a path in the initial Stokes diagram, the parallel transport along which defines a linear map (a number in this explicit case).",
    "Let us detail this process in the example drawn in Figure 12.",
    "Notice that the path associated to the Stokes arrow is closed here, but its inverse image in the picture before Fourier transform is not.",
    "The path on the left corresponds to the identity map."
  ]
}